Despite people claiming I never use scents in my stories, it does play a distinct role.
The question is how strong you make that ability. Most casual scents fade quickly in daylight or outside; depending on the outside weather it could be as little as a few days before bloodhound tracking isn't reliable enough.
I don't see any anthro - period - as ever having that degree of smell on top of bipedalism. Some would be better at "smell language" in the same way that some humans are adept at body language, or that a musician is better able to detect the subtlies of a piece versus an untrained ear.
